    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king #Patricius" ref="#people/14">Carolus</persName>
                        gratia Dei <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> Francorum et Langobadorum ac <rs
                            key="#Patricius">patricius</rs> Romanorum omnibus fidelibus nostris tam
                        presentibus quamque futuris. Si ea, que erga locis venerabilibus per
                        strumenta anteriorum regum iuste ac rationabiliter largita vel condonata
                        sunt, nostro munimine confirmamus, regiam, inquit, exercimus consuetudinem,
                        atque hoc nobis ad eternam beatitudinem in Dei nomine pertinere confidimus.
                        Unde compertum sit omnium vestrorum magnitudini, qualiter venerabilis vir
                            <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Curtes #Tolls #Monasteries #Abbots"
                            ref="#people/49">Anselmus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> de <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        noncupante <orgName key="#Abbots #Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/47">
                            <placeName ref="#places/15" key="#Monasteries">Nonantola</placeName>
                        </orgName>, quod est constructum in onore omnium apostolorum et beati
                        Silvestri confessoris, situm in <rs key="#City_territory">terraturio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#City_territory" ref="#places/38">Motinense</placeName>,
                        clementiae regni nostri petiit, eo quod <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/48">Haixtulfus</persName> vel ceteri quondam reges ac
                        reliqui Deo timentes homines eorum res ad memoratum sanctum locum
                        condonassent. Idcirco memoratus abbas celsitudini, nostre, ut ecclesias duas
                        in onore <orgName
                            key="#Gualdi #Cereals #Wood #Hay/fodder #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1107">
                            <orgName
                                key="#Gualdi #Cereals #Wood #Hay/fodder #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/1108"><placeName
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                                    ref="#places/1590"><placeName key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches" ref="#places/3628"
                                        >Sancti
                                    Martini</placeName></placeName></orgName>
                        </orgName> sitas in ipsas fine Motinense una cum earum apendiciis, etiam et
                            <rs key="#Gualdi">waldora</rs>, <rs key="#Cereals">terris</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Wood">silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>, pascois,
                        saltora, confinibus, <rs key="#Fisheries">piscariis</rs> seu et <rs
                            key="#Ports #Fluvial_transport #Tolls">portatico</rs> illo de <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Fluvial_transport #Tolls"
                            ref="#estates/50"><placeName ref="#places/40"
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Exceptive #Fiscal_reserve #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Ports #Fluvial_transport #Tolls"
                                >Cive Nova</placeName></geogName>, que annue collegitur, etiam hoc,
                        quod per bonum hominum largietate ibidem iuste conlatum fuit aut in antea
                        delegatum fuerit, per nostrum preceptum, sicut in eorum anteriora decleratur
                        precepta, que anteriores reges ibidem delegaverunt, confirmare deberemus.
                        Cuis petitioni denegare noluimus, sed ita prestitisse atque in omnibus
                        confirmasse cognuscite. Precipientes enim iubemus, ut, sicut, in anteriorum
                        regum declaratur precepta, omnes res, que ad illo monasterio, ut superius
                        intimata legitur, pertinentur, etiam terris, waldora, silvis, saltora,
                        confinibus atque piscariis seu de portatico illo de Cive Nova, quod annoe
                        collegitur, vel quicquid nos seu, ut diximus, anteriores reges vel ceteri
                        homines ibidem delegavimus, cum omnia, quicquid dici vel nominari potest, in
                        quibuslibet locis hoc quieto ordine teneant atque possedeant, vel quicquid
                        exinde agere pro oportunitate ipsius monastirii voluerint, liberum in
                        omnibus perfruantur arbitrium, quatenus melius eis delectet pro nobis etiam
                        fidelibus nostri Domini misericordia adtentius exorare. Et ut certius
                        credatis, de anulo nostro subter sigellavimus <persName key="#Notary"><name
                                ref="Ghiltbertus">Giltbertus</name></persName> advicem <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Rado">Radoni</name></persName> recognovi et
                        s. Data V Kalendas Augustas anno XII et septimo regni nostri; actum
                            <placeName key="#Palatium" ref="#places/4227">Lippia
                            Gyspringae</placeName> in <placeName>Saxonia</placeName>, in Dei
                        nominine feliciter. Amen semper.</ab>
